00:49:50.950 --> 00:49:52.720 align:middle line:90%
It reinforces that.

00:49:52.720 --> 00:49:55.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to listen to
the media that challenges it.

00:49:55.950 --> 00:49:57.677 align:middle line:90%
And vice versa is true.

00:49:57.677 --> 00:49:58.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:49:58.260 --> 00:50:00.500 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: So the
first thing is I'm

00:50:00.500 --> 00:50:04.820 align:middle line:90%
looking for a confirmation bias.

00:50:04.820 --> 00:50:08.150 align:middle line:84%
That confirmation bias
is such that I only

00:50:08.150 --> 00:50:13.020 align:middle line:84%
want information that reinforces
what I already believe.

00:50:13.020 --> 00:50:16.090 align:middle line:84%
You give me the sound bite, and
I'll take the sound bite out

00:50:16.090 --> 00:50:18.240 align:middle line:84%
