requires that I stop, evaluate,

00:51:15.470 --> 00:51:20.450 align:middle line:84%
analyze, consider the
ramifications, and so forth.

00:51:20.450 --> 00:51:23.170 align:middle line:84%
How much of our thinking is
of that kind of thinking?

00:51:23.170 --> 00:51:24.575 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Takes too much time.

00:51:24.575 --> 00:51:26.200 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Takes too
much time is right.

00:51:26.200 --> 00:51:29.700 align:middle line:84%
So we go through our
lives on automatic.

00:51:29.700 --> 00:51:32.290 align:middle line:90%
And the automatic is the script.

00:51:32.290 --> 00:51:35.340 align:middle line:90%
And the script isn't who I am.

00:51:35.340 --> 00:51:38.620 align:middle line:84%
It's all the stuff that
I've accumulated, including

00:51:38.620 --> 00:51:41.800 align:middle line:84%
the stuff I've taken
out of the media.

00:51:41.800 --> 00:51:46.580 align:middle line:84%
So in this little
book, "Self-hypnosis,"

00:51:46.580 --> 00:51:49.600 align:middle line:84%
I show you that when you sit
down in front of the television

00:51:49.600 --> 00:51:50.520 align:middle line:90%
set--

00:51:50.520 --> 00:51:53.330 align:middle line:84%
We've actually conducted
studies to try and get you

