So she says to the male eagle,
well, if I'm really an eagle,

00:56:25.460 --> 00:56:28.925 align:middle line:84%
then you're not going to
do me any harm, are you?

00:56:28.925 --> 00:56:30.255 align:middle line:90%
Of course not, he answers.

00:56:30.255 --> 00:56:32.560 align:middle line:90%
I'm not here to hurt you.

00:56:32.560 --> 00:56:34.330 align:middle line:90%
I'm here to help you.

00:56:34.330 --> 00:56:39.040 align:middle line:84%
Well, if that's the instance,
then you'll get out of my way.

00:56:39.040 --> 00:56:42.632 align:middle line:84%
You won't block me if I
wanted to leave, will you?

00:56:42.632 --> 00:56:44.295 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm not going to hurt you.

00:56:44.295 --> 00:56:45.745 align:middle line:90%
Look, I'll step over here.

00:56:45.745 --> 00:56:49.510 align:middle line:84%
And as he steps, she runs
to the chicken house.

00:56:49.510 --> 00:56:54.170 align:middle line:84%
Safe inside the chicken house,
she tells all her chicken

00:56:54.170 --> 00:56:58.040 align:middle line:84%
friends how she
outsmarted the eagle.

00:56:58.040 --> 00:56:59.760 align:middle line:90%
And they all, wow!

00:56:59.760 --> 00:57:02.160 align:middle line:90%
Good job!

00:57:02.160 --> 00:57:05.090 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you think about
that story for a minute,

00:57:05.090 --> 00:57:07.405 align:middle line:84%
and you think about
yourself, were

00:57:07.405 --> 00:57:11.530 align:middle line:84%
you raised with any of the
same thing I was raised with?

00:57:11.530 --> 00:57:16.010 align:middle line:84%
The negative scripting,
the chicken yard beliefs?

00:57:16.010 --> 00:57:18.720 align:middle line:90%
You're not smart enough.

00:57:18.720 --> 00:57:20.410 align:middle line:90%
You're not old enough.

00:57:20.410 --> 00:57:23.140 align:middle line:90%
You're not good looking enough.

00:57:23.140 --> 00:57:25.356 align:middle line:90%
You're too stupid.

00:57:25.356 --> 00:57:27.880 align:middle line:90%
You don't try hard enough.

00:57:27.880 --> 00:57:29.950 align:middle line:90%
That's not good.

00:57:29.950 --> 00:57:31.940 align:middle line:90%
This is evil.

00:57:31.940 --> 00:57:34.222 align:middle line:90%
That's bad.

00:57:34.222 --> 00:57:40.840 align:middle line:84%
You do understand, then, that if
you have chicken yard beliefs,

00:57:40.840 --> 00:57:46.850 align:middle line:84%
those beliefs can block you from
realizing what you might want

00:57:46.850 --> 00:57:52.874 align:middle line:84%
in life, and what you're
entitled to, your highest best.

00:57:52.874 --> 00:57:55.780 align:middle line:90%


00:57:55.780 --> 00:57:58.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So in "Choices
and Illusions," and we

00:57:58.050 --> 00:58:00.350 align:middle line:84%
just saw video that
talked about choice,

00:58:00.350 --> 00:58:02.590 align:middle line:84%
and the choices that
we make, and how

00:58:02.590 --> 00:58:03.590 align:middle line:90%
we have a higher choice.

00:58:03.590 --> 00:58:06.090 align:middle line:84%
But what about the
illusion part of it?

00:58:06.090 --> 00:58:08.580 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: OK, there
are probably a couple

00:58:08.580 --> 00:58:09.990 align:middle line:90%
of ways I can look at this.

00:58:09.990 --> 00:58:14.660 align:middle line:84%
The first one is if I have a
choice, as Krishnamurti said,

00:58:14.660 --> 00:58:18.182 align:middle line:84%
it arises as a
result of confusion.

00:58:18.182 --> 00:58:19.332 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:58:19.332 --> 00:58:20.290 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: Do I do this?

00:58:20.290 --> 00:58:22.060 align:middle line:90%
Or do I do that?

00:58:22.060 --> 00:58:24.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's obviously
a state of confusion.

00:58:24.210 --> 00:58:25.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm hm.

00:58:25.170 --> 00:58:27.150 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: If I know,
clearly, what I should do,

00:58:27.150 --> 00:58:29.140 align:middle line:90%
there isn't really a choice.

00:58:29.140 --> 00:58:31.040 align:middle line:90%
I do clearly what I should do.

00:58:31.040 --> 00:58:33.900 align:middle line:84%
Well most of us in our
lifetimes have never

00:58:33.900 --> 00:58:36.650 align:middle line:84%
really looked at
our life to say,

00:58:36.650 --> 00:58:40.070 align:middle line:84%
what is it that I should
do in all instances that

00:58:40.070 --> 00:58:43.240 align:middle line:84%
is the good of my life,
the good of humanity?

00:58:43.240 --> 00:58:44.756 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how do I
define my behavior?

00:58:44.756 --> 00:58:46.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We don't
think that far--

00:58:46.130 --> 00:58:48.230 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: We have
not sat down and made

00:58:48.230 --> 00:58:51.070 align:middle line:84%
a plan for how we're
going to live our lives.

00:58:51.070 --> 00:58:54.780 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to interact
every day in a positive way?

00:58:54.780 --> 00:58:57.330 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to help
other people in a positive?

00:58:57.330 --> 00:58:59.470 align:middle line:84%
One message, the
bottom line message

00:58:59.470 --> 00:59:01.960 align:middle line:84%
in "Choices and Illusions,"
as far as I'm concerned,

00:59:01.960 --> 00:59:04.860 align:middle line:84%
comes down to
convolute the model.

00:59:04.860 --> 00:59:07.360 align:middle line:84%
If you want to be successful,
think back to John

00:59:07.360 --> 00:59:10.290 align:middle line:84%
F Kennedy. "It's not what
my country can do for me,

00:59:10.290 --> 00:59:11.940 align:middle line:84%
but what I could
do for me country."

00:59:11.940 --> 00:59:13.520 align:middle line:84%
Don't think about
what is and I'm

00:59:13.520 --> 00:59:14.760 align:middle line:90%
going to get out of the day?

00:59:14.760 --> 00:59:17.330 align:middle line:84%
Think about what it is
you can bring to the day.

00:59:17.330 --> 00:59:20.420 align:middle line:84%
What is it that you
can give to the day.

00:59:20.420 --> 00:59:22.910 align:middle line:84%
I tell everybody, look, when
you wake up in the morning,

00:59:22.910 --> 00:59:25.190 align:middle line:90%
do this simple exercise.

00:59:25.190 --> 00:59:27.910 align:middle line:84%
Begin the day by saying, as
soon as you open your eyes,

00:59:27.910 --> 00:59:29.780 align:middle line:90%
thank you, thank you, thank you.

00:59:29.780 --> 00:59:31.530 align:middle line:90%
That changes your whole mindset.

00:59:31.530 --> 00:59:34.400 align:middle line:84%
And put the biggest smile
you can on your face.

00:59:34.400 --> 00:59:36.220 align:middle line:90%
Fake it, you know?

00:59:36.220 --> 00:59:39.000 align:middle line:84%
Big smile, because the
brain doesn't know you're

00:59:39.000 --> 00:59:40.860 align:middle line:90%
faking that smile.

00:59:40.860 --> 00:59:44.890 align:middle line:84%
The brain responds to
the facial contortion

00:59:44.890 --> 00:59:49.730 align:middle line:84%
by pumping on endorphins, the
body's natural opiate system.

00:59:49.730 --> 00:59:51.440 align:middle line:90%
So I then begin to feel good.

00:59:51.440 --> 00:59:51.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:59:51.940 --> 00:59:52.523 align:middle line:90%
>>TAYLOR: See?

00:59:52.523 --> 00:59:55.170 align:middle line:90%
And that's how I start my day.

00:59:55.170 --> 00:59:57.035 align:middle line:84%
Well, again I'm going
to tell a quick story.

00:59:57.035 --> 00:59:57.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:59:57.310 --> 00:59:58.370 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I'll
make it real fast.

00:59:58.370 --> 00:59:59.067 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:59:59.067 --> 01:00:00.900 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I had a young
woman referred to me

01:00:00.900 --> 01:00:07.075 align:middle line:84%
years ago by a psychiatrist who
was on a lot of pharmacology,

01:00:07.075 --> 01:00:11.340 align:middle line:84%
a lot of medication,
because she was suicidal.

01:00:11.340 --> 01:00:16.630 align:middle line:84%
And she had, on many
occasions, mutilated herself.

01:00:16.630 --> 01:00:20.150 align:middle line:84%
So when she came into my
office the first time,

01:00:20.150 --> 01:00:21.720 align:middle line:84%
I looked at her
intake sheets and I

01:00:21.720 --> 01:00:24.770 align:middle line:84%
saw that her first clinician
was Milton Erickson.

01:00:24.770 --> 01:00:25.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

01:00:25.360 --> 01:00:27.568 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Now, to me, Milton
Erickson walks on water.

01:00:27.568 --> 01:00:30.350 align:middle line:84%
So I honestly asked
myself, Lisa, what on earth

01:00:30.350 --> 01:00:31.600 align:middle line:90%
am I supposed to do with this?

01:00:31.600 --> 01:00:32.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What did he not?

01:00:32.600 --> 01:00:34.390 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, yeah.

01:00:34.390 --> 01:00:37.650 align:middle line:84%
Ericksonian hypnosis, and
the-- yeah, very classic.

01:00:37.650 --> 01:00:39.975 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: The guy
walks on water, period.

01:00:39.975 --> 01:00:41.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, very,
very brilliant.

01:00:41.470 --> 01:00:44.240 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: You know, I'm sitting
there thinking about this.

01:00:44.240 --> 01:00:46.740 align:middle line:84%
And I decided I'm going to do
something entirely different.

01:00:46.740 --> 01:00:50.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can call this
perspiration or inspiration,

01:00:50.020 --> 01:00:51.420 align:middle line:90%
whichever you want.

01:00:51.420 --> 01:00:53.434 align:middle line:84%
But when she came in,
I told her, you know,

01:00:53.434 --> 01:00:55.350 align:middle line:84%
we're going to do what's
called brief therapy.

01:00:55.350 --> 01:00:57.045 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to only
see you 10 times.

01:00:57.045 --> 01:00:58.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to see
you over 10 weeks.

01:00:58.780 --> 01:01:00.070 align:middle line:90%
You're going to have homework.

01:01:00.070 --> 01:01:02.070 align:middle line:10%
And of course, you know
the power or suggestion,

01:01:02.070 --> 01:01:03.737 align:middle line:10%
this is absolutely
going to be reversed.

01:01:03.737 --> 01:01:05.403 align:middle line:10%
And you will be bah,
bah, bah, bah, bah.

01:01:05.403 --> 01:01:06.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:01:06.050 --> 01:01:07.508 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: But here's
your homework.

01:01:07.508 --> 01:01:10.000 align:middle line:84%
This was the magic,
not what I was saying.

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:15.680 align:middle line:84%
I want you to get a diary,
a journal, a notebook.

01:01:15.680 --> 01:01:19.370 align:middle line:84%
And every day this week, I want
to do a good deed for someone

01:01:19.370 --> 01:01:20.460 align:middle line:90%
you don't know.

01:01:20.460 --> 01:01:21.905 align:middle line:90%
You just do a good deed.

01:01:21.905 --> 01:01:23.530 align:middle line:84%
Go out of your way
to do the good deed.

01:01:23.530 --> 01:01:24.710 align:middle line:90%
I don't care what it is.

01:01:24.710 --> 01:01:27.900 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's change and somebody's
short at the cash register.

01:01:27.900 --> 01:01:29.980 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's helping
somebody across the street.

01:01:29.980 --> 01:01:33.050 align:middle line:90%
Find a way to do a good deed.

01:01:33.050 --> 01:01:37.640 align:middle line:84%
And then, in the evening,
write it in your journal.

01:01:37.640 --> 01:01:40.910 align:middle line:84%
I want you to then think
about that good deed,

01:01:40.910 --> 01:01:43.350 align:middle line:84%
how it made you feel,
and how the person who

01:01:43.350 --> 01:01:45.650 align:middle line:84%
received the good
deed might have felt.

01:01:45.650 --> 01:01:48.960 align:middle line:84%
I don't care if they're
anonymous, even, good deeds.

01:01:48.960 --> 01:01:50.700 align:middle line:10%
But I want you to put
it in that journal.

01:01:50.700 --> 01:01:53.930 align:middle line:10%
And after you've completed
your thinking process,

01:01:53.930 --> 01:01:56.082 align:middle line:10%
then close your
eyes, go to sleep.

01:01:56.082 --> 01:01:57.630 align:middle line:84%
I want you to go
to sleep on that.

01:01:57.630 --> 01:01:58.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:01:58.130 --> 01:02:00.980 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Week two,
I want you to do two.

01:02:00.980 --> 01:02:02.610 align:middle line:90%
Week three, it was three.

01:02:02.610 --> 01:02:05.650 align:middle line:84%
We got up to five, but
she didn't always do five.

01:02:05.650 --> 01:02:08.240 align:middle line:90%
But here was the difference.

01:02:08.240 --> 01:02:10.787 align:middle line:84%
This woman came in with
very low self esteem.

01:02:10.787 --> 01:02:11.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm hm.

01:02:11.370 --> 01:02:11.890 align:middle line:90%
Mm hm.

01:02:11.890 --> 01:02:13.440 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: She didn't
deserve to live.

01:02:13.440 --> 01:02:14.523 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's the bottom.

01:02:14.523 --> 01:02:15.850 align:middle line:90%
That's how she would define it.

01:02:15.850 --> 01:02:18.480 align:middle line:84%
She had stories and
reasons for that.

01:02:18.480 --> 01:02:21.604 align:middle line:84%
And she truly had a tragic
story in the background.

01:02:21.604 --> 01:02:22.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So she had evidence.

01:02:22.770 --> 01:02:24.780 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: But everybody
deserves to live.

01:02:24.780 --> 01:02:28.130 align:middle line:84%
And everybody deserves
to live to their fullest.

01:02:28.130 --> 01:02:33.570 align:middle line:84%
But in order for you to
recognize what your worth is,

01:02:33.570 --> 01:02:36.650 align:middle line:84%
you often have to do
something for someone else.

01:02:36.650 --> 01:02:39.290 align:middle line:84%
In other words, you
can't fill yourself up

01:02:39.290 --> 01:02:41.780 align:middle line:90%
by just patting on your back.

01:02:41.780 --> 01:02:44.550 align:middle line:84%
But when you begin
to help others,

01:02:44.550 --> 01:02:47.640 align:middle line:84%
what you find is that as
you're giving them something,

01:02:47.640 --> 01:02:49.590 align:middle line:90%
you're making a difference.

01:02:49.590 --> 01:02:52.840 align:middle line:84%
And in making that
difference, your life matters.

01:02:52.840 --> 01:02:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And in that process, you
begin to fill yourself

01:02:57.070 --> 01:02:57.970 align:middle line:90%
from the inside.

01:02:57.970 --> 01:03:02.350 align:middle line:84%
You begin to realize
that you're important,

01:03:02.350 --> 01:03:05.540 align:middle line:84%
that you can make
the difference.

01:03:05.540 --> 01:03:08.820 align:middle line:84%
And by taking that into
your sleep every night,

01:03:08.820 --> 01:03:12.850 align:middle line:84%
you're priming yourself,
you're priming your psychology

01:03:12.850 --> 01:03:15.030 align:middle line:90%
to recognize that.

01:03:15.030 --> 01:03:16.584 align:middle line:84%
This woman turned
her life around.

01:03:16.584 --> 01:03:17.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: She did?

01:03:17.250 --> 01:03:19.100 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: I followed
or for three years.

01:03:19.100 --> 01:03:23.850 align:middle line:84%
She was off of all
pharmacology three years out.

01:03:23.850 --> 01:03:28.590 align:middle line:84%
She finished her 10 weeks with
me, never cut herself again,

01:03:28.590 --> 01:03:30.950 align:middle line:90%
never attempted suicide again.

01:03:30.950 --> 01:03:34.750 align:middle line:84%
Because she learned
that she was valuable.

01:03:34.750 --> 01:03:39.900 align:middle line:84%
That's how you discover how
your own worth is built.

01:03:39.900 --> 01:03:41.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How it's self value.

01:03:41.730 --> 01:03:44.180 align:middle line:90%
And self love, and value.

01:03:44.180 --> 01:03:46.650 align:middle line:84%
That is, I think,
the beautiful thing

01:03:46.650 --> 01:03:49.680 align:middle line:84%
of where you've come
from, what you've seen,

01:03:49.680 --> 01:03:51.350 align:middle line:84%
how you've turned
your own life around.

01:03:51.350 --> 01:03:54.890 align:middle line:84%
And then how you teach us to
do it, and teach the masses how

01:03:54.890 --> 01:03:57.320 align:middle line:84%
to do it, which is
inspirational to me.

01:03:57.320 --> 01:03:58.825 align:middle line:84%
So thank you so
much for being here.

01:03:58.825 --> 01:03:59.620 align:middle line:84%
>>TAYLOR: Oh, it's
been my pleasure.

01:03:59.620 --> 01:04:00.450 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

01:04:00.450 --> 01:04:02.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I could talk to you and
listen to your stories forever.

01:04:02.490 --> 01:04:04.781 align:middle line:84%
But if you would like to
watch a replay of my interview

01:04:04.781 --> 01:04:06.970 align:middle line:84%
with Eldon Taylor, or
share it with your friends,

01:04:06.970 --> 01:04:08.920 align:middle line:90%
go to gaiamtv.com.

01:04:08.920 --> 01:04:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And until next time, I
invite you to stay inspired.

